Test Case 2:

Viscoelastic die swell in cylindrical geometry

Description:
Fluid enters at left geometry under fully developed conditions.
Lower boundary is a symmetry (r=0) plane.  Upper boundary is
no slip for half its length and the becomes a kinematic surface.
Fluid swells as it exits pipe.

Two viscoelastic fluid models can be used, giesekus or phan thien
tanner.  Switching between them is accomplished by commenting and
uncommenting several cards in the input deck

Features:
A TABLE_BC card is used to specify the inlet non-newtonian velocity
profiles.  These are contained in the files giesekus_inlet.table 
and ptt_inlet.table.  The velocity profiles here are specific to the
parameters appearing in giesekus.mat or ptt.mat.  These files
should not be changed.

Portions of code exercise:

Viscoelasticity, viscoelasticity and free surfaces, TABLE_BC boundary
conditions.

Solution method:

UMF 

Runtime:

Runtime on the compute server( sass2153) is roughly 5 minutes
for both fluid models.


Files:

input			input deck for both fluids
newtonian_swell.exoII	newtonain die swell solution used as starting guess
solution_ptt.exoII	phan thien tanner solution file
solution_giesekus.exoII	giesekus solutino file
giesekus.mat		giesekus material file
ptt.mat			phan thien tanner material file
giesekus_inlet.table	inlet velocity profile for giesekus model	
ptt_inlet.table		inlet velocity profile for phan thien tanner model
giesekus_output.txt	goma screen output for giesekus model
ptt_output.txt		goma screen output for phan thien tanner model
